dom-idbcursor-advance.name: advance
dom-idbcursor-advance.summary: The advance() method of the IDBCursor interface sets the number of times a cursor should move its position forward.
dom-idbcursor-advance.title: IDBCursor.advance()

dom-idbcursor-continue.name: continue
dom-idbcursor-continue.summary: The continue() method of the IDBCursor interface advances the cursor to the next position along its direction, to the item whose key matches the optional key parameter. If no key is specified, the cursor advances to the immediate next position, based on its direction.
dom-idbcursor-continue.title: IDBCursor.continue()

dom-idbcursor-delete.name: delete
dom-idbcursor-delete.summary: The delete() method of the IDBCursor interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, deletes the record at the cursor's position, without changing the cursor's position. Once the record is deleted, the cursor's value is set to null.
dom-idbcursor-delete.title: IDBCursor.delete()

dom-idbcursor-direction.name: direction
dom-idbcursor-direction.summary: The direction read-only property of the IDBCursor interface is a DOMString that returns the direction of traversal of the cursor (set using IDBObjectStore.openCursor for example). See the Values section below for possible values.
dom-idbcursor-direction.title: IDBCursor.direction

dom-idbcursor-key.name: key
dom-idbcursor-key.summary: The key read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the key for the record at the cursor's position. If the cursor is outside its range, this is set to undefined. The cursor's key can be any data type.
dom-idbcursor-key.title: IDBCursor.key

dom-idbcursor-primarykey.name: primaryKey
dom-idbcursor-primarykey.summary: The primaryKey read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the cursor's current effective key. If the cursor is currently being iterated or has iterated outside its range, this is set to undefined. The cursor's primary key can be any data type.
dom-idbcursor-primarykey.title: IDBCursor.primaryKey

dom-idbcursor-source.name: source
dom-idbcursor-source.summary: The source read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the IDBObjectStore or IDBIndex that the cursor is iterating over. This function never returns null or throws an exception, even if the cursor is currently being iterated, has iterated past its end, or its transaction is not active.
dom-idbcursor-source.title: IDBCursor.source

dom-idbcursor-update.name: update
dom-idbcursor-update.summary: The update() method of the IDBCursor interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, updates the value at the current position of the cursor in the object store. If the cursor points to a record that has just been deleted, a new record is created.
dom-idbcursor-update.title: IDBCursor.update()

cursor-interface.name: IDBCursor
cursor-interface.summary: The IDBCursor interface of the IndexedDB API represents a cursor for traversing or iterating over multiple records in a database.
cursor-interface.title: IDBCursor

dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value.name: value
dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value.summary: The value read-only property of the IDBCursorWithValue interface returns the value of the current cursor, whatever that is.
dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value.title: IDBCursorWithValue.value

idbcursorwithvalue.name: IDBCursorWithValue
idbcursorwithvalue.summary: The IDBCursorWithValue interface of the IndexedDB API represents a cursor for traversing or iterating over multiple records in a database. It is the same as the IDBCursor, except that it includes the value property.
idbcursorwithvalue.title: IDBCursorWithValue

dom-idbdatabase-close.name: close
dom-idbdatabase-close.summary: The close() method of the IDBDatabase interface returns immediately and closes the connection in a separate thread.
dom-idbdatabase-close.title: IDBDatabase.close()

dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstore.name: createObjectStore
dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstore.summary: The createObjectStore() method of the IDBDatabase interface creates and returns a new object store or index.
dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstore.title: IDBDatabase.createObjectStore()

dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstore.name: deleteObjectStore
dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstore.summary: The deleteObjectStore() method of the IDBDatabase interface destroys the object store with the given name in the connected database, along with any indexes that reference it.
dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstore.title: IDBDatabase.deleteObjectStore()

dom-idbdatabase-name.name: name
dom-idbdatabase-name.summary: The name read-only property of the IDBDatabase interface is a DOMString that contains the name of the connected database.
dom-idbdatabase-name.title: IDBDatabase.name

dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.name: objectStoreNames
dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.summary: The objectStoreNames read-only property of the IDBDatabase interface is a DOMStringList containing a list of the names of the object stores currently in the connected database.
dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.title: IDBDatabase.objectStoreNames

dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.name: objectStoreNames
dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.summary: The objectStoreNames read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns a DOMStringList of names of IDBObjectStore objects.
dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.title: IDBTransaction.objectStoreNames

dom-idbdatabase-onabort.name: onabort
dom-idbdatabase-onabort.summary: The onabort event handler of the IDBDatabase interface handles the abort event, fired when a transaction is aborted and bubbles up to the connection object.
dom-idbdatabase-onabort.title: IDBDatabase.onabort

dom-idbdatabase-onerror.name: onerror
dom-idbdatabase-onerror.summary: The onerror event handler of the IDBDatabase interface handles the error event, fired when a request returns an error and bubbles up to the connection object.
dom-idbdatabase-onerror.title: IDBDatabase.onerror

dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.name: onversionchange
dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.summary: The onversionchange event handler of the IDBDatabase interface handles the versionchange event, fired when a database structure change (IDBOpenDBRequest.onupgradeneeded event or IDBFactory.deleteDatabase) was requested elsewhere (most probably in another window/tab on the same computer).
dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.title: IDBDatabase.onversionchange

dom-idbdatabase-transaction.name: transaction
dom-idbdatabase-transaction.summary: The transaction method of the IDBDatabase interface immediately returns a transaction object (IDBTransaction) containing the IDBTransaction.objectStore method, which you can use to access your object store.
dom-idbdatabase-transaction.title: IDBDatabase.transaction()

dom-idbdatabase-version.name: version
dom-idbdatabase-version.summary: The version property of the IDBDatabase interface is a 64-bit integer that contains the version of the connected database. When a database is first created, this attribute is an empty string.
dom-idbdatabase-version.title: IDBDatabase.version

idbdatabase.name: IDBDatabase
idbdatabase.summary: The IDBDatabase interface of the IndexedDB API provides a connection to a database; you can use an IDBDatabase object to open a transaction on your database then create, manipulate, and delete objects (data) in that database. The interface provides the only way to get and manage versions of the database.
idbdatabase.title: IDBDatabase

dom-idbfactory-cmp.name: cmp
dom-idbfactory-cmp.summary: The cmp() method of the IDBFactory interface compares two values as keys to determine equality and ordering for IndexedDB operations, such as storing and iterating.
dom-idbfactory-cmp.title: IDBFactory.cmp()

dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase.name: deleteDatabase
dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase.summary: The deleteDatabase() method of the IDBFactory interface requests the deletion of a database. The method returns an IDBOpenDBRequest object immediately, and performs the deletion operation asynchronously.
dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase.title: IDBFactory.deleteDatabase()

dom-idbfactory-open.name: open
dom-idbfactory-open.summary: The open() method of the IDBFactory interface requests opening a connection to a database.
dom-idbfactory-open.title: IDBFactory.open()

dom-idbindex-count.name: count
dom-idbindex-count.summary: The count() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and in a separate thread, returns the number of records within a key range.
dom-idbindex-count.title: IDBIndex.count()

dom-idbindex-get.name: get
dom-idbindex-get.summary: The get() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, finds either the value in the referenced object store that corresponds to the given key or the first corresponding value, if key is set to an IDBKeyRange.
dom-idbindex-get.title: IDBIndex.get()

dom-idbindex-getkey.name: getKey
dom-idbindex-getkey.summary: The getKey() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, finds either the primary key that corresponds to the given key in this index or the first corresponding primary key, if key is set to an IDBKeyRange.
dom-idbindex-getkey.title: IDBIndex.getKey()

dom-idbindex-keypath.name: keyPath
dom-idbindex-keypath.summary: The keyPath property of the IDBIndex interface returns the key path of the current index. If null, this index is not auto-populated.
dom-idbindex-keypath.title: IDBIndex.keyPath

dom-idbindex-multientry.name: multiEntry
dom-idbindex-multientry.summary: The multiEntry read-only property of the IDBIndex interface returns a boolean value that affects how the index behaves when the result of evaluating the index's key path yields an array.
dom-idbindex-multientry.title: IDBIndex.multiEntry

dom-idbindex-name.name: name
dom-idbindex-name.summary: The name property of the IDBIndex interface contains a string which names the index.
dom-idbindex-name.title: IDBIndex.name

dom-idbindex-objectstore.name: objectStore
dom-idbindex-objectstore.summary: The objectStore property of the IDBIndex interface returns the name of the object store referenced by the current index.
dom-idbindex-objectstore.title: IDBIndex.objectStore

dom-idbindex-opencursor.name: openCursor
dom-idbindex-opencursor.summary: The openCursor() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a cursor over the specified key range.
dom-idbindex-opencursor.title: IDBIndex.openCursor()

dom-idbindex-opencursor.name: openCursor
dom-idbindex-opencursor.summary: The openCursor() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns a new IDBCursorWithValue object. Used for iterating through an object store with a cursor.
dom-idbindex-opencursor.title: IDBObjectStore.openCursor()

dom-idbindex-openkeycursor.name: openKeyCursor
dom-idbindex-openkeycursor.summary: The openKeyCursor() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a cursor over the specified key range, as arranged by this index.
dom-idbindex-openkeycursor.title: IDBIndex.openKeyCursor()

dom-idbindex-unique.name: unique
dom-idbindex-unique.summary: The unique read-only property returns a boolean that states whether the index allows duplicate keys.
dom-idbindex-unique.title: IDBIndex.unique

idbindex.name: IDBIndex
idbindex.summary: IDBIndex interface of the IndexedDB API provides asynchronous access to an index in a database. An index is a kind of object store for looking up records in another object store, called the referenced object store. You use this interface to retrieve data.
idbindex.title: IDBIndex

dom-idbkeyrange-bound.name: bound
dom-idbkeyrange-bound.summary: The bound() method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new key range with the specified upper and lower bounds. The bounds can be open (that is, the bounds exclude the endpoint values) or closed (that is, the bounds include the endpoint values). By default, the bounds are closed.
dom-idbkeyrange-bound.title: IDBKeyRange.bound()

dom-idbkeyrange-lower.name: lower
dom-idbkeyrange-lower.summary: The lower read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns the lower bound of the key range.
dom-idbkeyrange-lower.title: IDBKeyRange.lower

dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen.name: lowerOpen
dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen.summary: The lowerOpen read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns a boolean indicating whether the lower-bound value is included in the key range.
dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen.title: IDBKeyRange.lowerOpen

dom-idbkeyrange-only.name: only
dom-idbkeyrange-only.summary: The only() method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new key range containing a single value.
dom-idbkeyrange-only.title: IDBKeyRange.only()

dom-idbkeyrange-upper.name: upper
dom-idbkeyrange-upper.summary: The upper read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns the upper bound of the key range.
dom-idbkeyrange-upper.title: IDBKeyRange.upper

dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen.name: upperOpen
dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen.summary: The upperOpen read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns a boolean indicating whether the upper-bound value is included in the key range.
dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen.title: IDBKeyRange.upperOpen

idbkeyrange.name: IDBKeyRange
idbkeyrange.summary: The IDBKeyRange interface of the IndexedDB API represents a continuous interval over some data type that is used for keys. Records can be retrieved from IDBObjectStore and IDBIndex objects using keys or a range of keys. You can limit the range using lower and upper bounds. For example, you can iterate over all values of a key in the value range AZ.
idbkeyrange.title: IDBKeyRange

dom-idbobjectstore-add.name: add
dom-idbobjectstore-add.summary: The add() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a structured clone of the value, and stores the cloned value in the object store. This is for adding new records to an object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-add.title: IDBObjectStore.add()

dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.name: autoIncrement
dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.summary: The autoIncrement read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the value of the auto increment flag for this object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.title: IDBObjectStore.autoIncrement

dom-idbobjectstore-clear.name: clear
dom-idbobjectstore-clear.summary: The clear() method of the IDBObjectStore interface creates and immediately returns an IDBRequest object, and clears this object store in a separate thread. This is for deleting all the current data out of an object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-clear.title: IDBObjectStore.clear()

dom-idbobjectstore-count.name: count
dom-idbobjectstore-count.summary: The count() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns the total number of records that match the provided key or IDBKeyRange. If no arguments are provided, it returns the total number of records in the store.
dom-idbobjectstore-count.title: IDBObjectStore.count()

dom-idbobjectstore-createindex.name: createIndex
dom-idbobjectstore-createindex.summary: The createIndex() method of the IDBObjectStore interface creates and returns a new IDBIndex object in the connected database. It creates a new field/column defining a new data point for each database record to contain.
dom-idbobjectstore-createindex.title: IDBObjectStore.createIndex()

dom-idbobjectstore-delete.name: delete
dom-idbobjectstore-delete.summary: The delete() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, deletes the specified record or records.
dom-idbobjectstore-delete.title: IDBObjectStore.delete()

dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex.name: deleteIndex
dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex.summary: The deleteIndex() method of the IDBObjectStore interface destroys the index with the specified name in the connected database, used during a version upgrade.
dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex.title: IDBObjectStore.deleteIndex()

dom-idbobjectstore-get.name: get
dom-idbobjectstore-get.summary: The get() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns the object store selected by the specified key. This is for retrieving specific records from an object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-get.title: IDBObjectStore.get()

dom-idbobjectstore-index.name: index
dom-idbobjectstore-index.summary: The index() method of the IDBObjectStore interface opens a named index in the current object store, after which it can be used to, for example, return a series of records sorted by that index using a cursor.
dom-idbobjectstore-index.title: IDBObjectStore.index()

dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames.name: indexNames
dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames.summary: The indexNames read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns a list of the names of indexes on objects in this object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames.title: IDBObjectStore.indexNames

dom-idbobjectstore-keypath.name: keyPath
dom-idbobjectstore-keypath.summary: The keyPath read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the key path of this object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-keypath.title: IDBObjectStore.keyPath

dom-idbobjectstore-name.name: name
dom-idbobjectstore-name.summary: The name property of the IDBObjectStore interface indicates the name of this object store.
dom-idbobjectstore-name.title: IDBObjectStore.name

dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.name: openKeyCursor
dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.summary: The openKeyCursor() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object whose result will be set to an IDBCursor that can be used to iterate through matching results. Used for iterating through the keys of an object store with a cursor.
dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.title: IDBObjectStore.openKeyCursor()

dom-idbobjectstore-put.name: put
dom-idbobjectstore-put.summary: The put() method of the IDBObjectStore interface updates a given record in a database, or inserts a new record if the given item does not already exist.
dom-idbobjectstore-put.title: IDBObjectStore.put()

dom-idbobjectstore-transaction.name: transaction
dom-idbobjectstore-transaction.summary: The transaction read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the transaction object to which this object store belongs.
dom-idbobjectstore-transaction.title: IDBObjectStore.transaction

idbobjectstore.name: IDBObjectStore
idbobjectstore.summary: The IDBObjectStore interface of the IndexedDB API represents an object store in a database. Records within an object store are sorted according to their keys. This sorting enables fast insertion, look-up, and ordered retrieval.
idbobjectstore.title: IDBObjectStore

dom-idbopendbrequest-onblocked.name: onblocked
dom-idbopendbrequest-onblocked.summary: The onblocked event handler of the IDBOpenDBRequest interface is the event handler for the blocked event. This event is triggered when the upgradeneeded should be triggered because of a version change but the database is still in use (that is, not closed) somewhere, even after the versionchange event was sent.
dom-idbopendbrequest-onblocked.title: IDBOpenDBRequest.onblocked

dom-idbopendbrequest-onupgradeneeded.name: onupgradeneeded
dom-idbopendbrequest-onupgradeneeded.summary: The onupgradeneeded property of the IDBOpenDBRequest interface is the event handler for the upgradeneeded event, triggered when a database of a bigger version number than the existing stored database is loaded.
dom-idbopendbrequest-onupgradeneeded.title: IDBOpenDBRequest.onupgradeneeded

idbopendbrequest.name: IDBOpenDBRequest
idbopendbrequest.summary: The IDBOpenDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to the results of requests to open or delete databases (performed using IDBFactory.open and IDBFactory.deleteDatabase), using specific event handler attributes.
idbopendbrequest.title: IDBOpenDBRequest

dom-idbrequest-error.name: error
dom-idbrequest-error.summary: The error read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the error in the event of an unsuccessful request.
dom-idbrequest-error.title: IDBRequest.error

dom-idbrequest-onerror.name: onerror
dom-idbrequest-onerror.summary: The onerror event handler of the IDBRequest interface handles the error event, fired when a request returns an error.
dom-idbrequest-onerror.title: IDBRequest.onerror

dom-idbrequest-onsuccess.name: onsuccess
dom-idbrequest-onsuccess.summary: The onsuccess event handler of the IDBRequest interface handles the success event, fired when the result of a request is successfully returned.
dom-idbrequest-onsuccess.title: IDBRequest.onsuccess

dom-idbrequest-readystate.name: readyState
dom-idbrequest-readystate.summary: The readyState read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the state of the request.
dom-idbrequest-readystate.title: IDBRequest.readyState

dom-idbrequest-result.name: result
dom-idbrequest-result.summary: The result read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the result of the request. If the request failed and the result is not available, an InvalidStateError exception is thrown.
dom-idbrequest-result.title: IDBRequest.result

dom-idbrequest-source.name: source
dom-idbrequest-source.summary: The source read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the source of the request, such as an Index or an object store. If no source exists (such as when calling indexedDB.open), it returns null.
dom-idbrequest-source.title: IDBRequest.source

dom-idbrequest-transaction.name: transaction
dom-idbrequest-transaction.summary: The transaction read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the transaction for the request, that is, the transaction the request is being made inside.
dom-idbrequest-transaction.title: IDBRequest.transaction

idbrequest.name: IDBRequest
idbrequest.summary: The IDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to results of asynchronous requests to databases and database objects using event handler attributes. Each reading and writing operation on a database is done using a request.
idbrequest.title: IDBRequest

dom-idbtransaction-abort.name: abort
dom-idbtransaction-abort.summary: The abort() method of the IDBTransaction interface rolls back all the changes to objects in the database associated with this transaction.
dom-idbtransaction-abort.title: IDBTransaction.abort()

dom-idbtransaction-db.name: db
dom-idbtransaction-db.summary: The db read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the database connection with which this transaction is associated.
dom-idbtransaction-db.title: IDBTransaction.db

dom-idbtransaction-error.name: error
dom-idbtransaction-error.summary: The IDBTransaction.error property of the IDBTransaction interface returns one of several types of error when there is an unsuccessful transaction.
dom-idbtransaction-error.title: IDBTransaction.error

dom-idbtransaction-mode.name: mode
dom-idbtransaction-mode.summary: The mode read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the current mode for accessing the data in the object stores in the scope of the transaction (i.e. is the mode to be read-only, or do you want to write to the object stores?) The default value is readonly.
dom-idbtransaction-mode.title: IDBTransaction.mode

dom-idbtransaction-objectstore.name: objectStore
dom-idbtransaction-objectstore.summary: The objectStore() method of the IDBTransaction interface returns an object store that has already been added to the scope of this transaction.
dom-idbtransaction-objectstore.title: IDBTransaction.objectStore()

dom-idbtransaction-onabort.name: onabort
dom-idbtransaction-onabort.summary: The onabort event handler of the IDBTransaction interface handles the abort event, fired, when the current transaction is aborted via the IDBTransaction.abort method.
dom-idbtransaction-onabort.title: IDBTransaction.onabort

dom-idbtransaction-oncomplete.name: oncomplete
dom-idbtransaction-oncomplete.summary: The oncomplete event handler of the IDBTransaction interface handles the complete event, fired when the transaction successfully completes.
dom-idbtransaction-oncomplete.title: IDBTransaction.oncomplete

dom-idbtransaction-onerror.name: onerror
dom-idbtransaction-onerror.summary: The onerror event handler of the IDBTransaction interface handles the error event, fired when a request returns an error and bubbles up to the transaction object.
dom-idbtransaction-onerror.title: IDBTransaction.onerror

transaction.name: IDBTransaction
transaction.summary: The IDBTransaction interface of the IndexedDB API provides a static, asynchronous transaction on a database using event handler attributes. All reading and writing of data is done within transactions. You use IDBDatabase to start transactions, IDBTransaction to set the mode of the transaction (e.g. is it readonly or readwrite), and you access an IDBObjectStore to make a request. You can also use an IDBTransaction object to abort transactions.
transaction.title: IDBTransaction

dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.name: newVersion
dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.summary: The newVersion read-only property of the IDBVersionChangeEvent interface returns the new version number of the database.
dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent.newVersion

dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.name: oldVersion
dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.summary: The oldVersion read-only property of the IDBVersionChangeEvent interface returns the old version number of the database.
dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent.oldVersion

idbversionchangeevent.name: IDBVersionChangeEvent
idbversionchangeevent.summary: The IDBVersionChangeEvent interface of the IndexedDB API indicates that the version of the database has changed, as the result of an IDBOpenDBRequest.onupgradeneeded event handler function.
idbversionchangeevent.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent

dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.name: indexedDB
dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.summary: The indexedDB read-only property of the WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope mixin provides a mechanism for applications to asynchronously access the capabilities of indexed databases.
dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.title: WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope.indexedDB
